884
00:48:58,205 --> 00:49:01,124
♪ He can't, he can!
He surely can't, he surely can't! ♪

885
00:49:01,208 --> 00:49:03,960
♪ You are the man, Bruce!
He might explode! ♪

886
00:49:04,586 --> 00:49:06,379
♪ He's quite elastic ♪

887
00:49:06,463 --> 00:49:08,423
♪ He's going to blow! Make him stop! ♪

888
00:49:08,506 --> 00:49:11,968
♪ He's fantastic, look at him go!
I can't watch! ♪

889
00:49:12,051 --> 00:49:14,929
♪ I think in effect
This must confirm, Bruce ♪

890
00:49:15,012 --> 00:49:18,683
♪ What we all suspected
You have a worm, Bruce ♪

891
00:49:18,766 --> 00:49:22,103
♪ Or maybe your largeness
Is a bit like the Tardis ♪

892
00:49:22,603 --> 00:49:25,606
♪ Considerably roomier inside ♪

893
00:49:26,190 --> 00:49:27,441
♪ He can't! He can! ♪

894
00:49:27,524 --> 00:49:29,068
♪ He surely can't! He surely can't! ♪

895
00:49:29,151 --> 00:49:33,905
♪ You are the man, Bruce!
B-R-O-O-C-E ♪

896
00:49:33,990 --> 00:49:35,074
♪ Bruce! ♪

897
00:49:36,283 --> 00:49:40,079
♪ You'll never again be subject to abuse
For your immense caboose ♪

898
00:49:40,162 --> 00:49:42,539
♪ She'll call a truce, Bruce ♪

899
00:49:42,623 --> 00:49:45,876
♪ With every swallow you are
Tightening the noose ♪

900
00:49:45,959 --> 00:49:48,504
♪ We never thought it was possible ♪

901
00:49:49,380 --> 00:49:51,923
♪ But here it is coming true ♪

902
00:49:52,007 --> 00:49:55,051
♪ We can have our cake and eat it too ♪

903
00:49:56,219 --> 00:49:58,805
♪ The time has come
To put that tumbly tum to use ♪

904
00:50:00,515 --> 00:50:02,768
♪ No excuse, Bruce ♪

905
00:50:02,851 --> 00:50:05,854
♪ Let out your belt
I think you'll want your trousers loose ♪

906
00:50:06,562 --> 00:50:08,314
♪ Ooooh, stuff it in! ♪

907
00:50:08,398 --> 00:50:09,607
-♪ Bruce! ♪
-♪ You've almost finished ♪

908
00:50:09,690 --> 00:50:10,733
-♪ Bruce! ♪
-♪ You'll fit it in ♪

909
00:50:10,816 --> 00:50:12,568
♪ Whatever you do just don't give in ♪

910
00:50:12,652 --> 00:50:14,237
-♪ Bruce! ♪
-♪ Don't let her win! ♪

911
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:17,240
♪ Come on, Bruce, be our hero ♪

912
00:50:17,323 --> 00:50:20,576
♪ Cover yourself in chocolate glory ♪

913
00:50:20,660 --> 00:50:21,494
♪ Bruce! ♪

914
00:50:22,787 --> 00:50:26,832
♪ You'll never again be subject to abuse
For your immense caboose ♪

915
00:50:26,916 --> 00:50:29,334
♪ She'll call a truce, Bruce! ♪

916
00:50:29,419 --> 00:50:32,588
♪ Just one more bite and you'll've
Completely cooked 'er goose ♪

917
00:50:32,672 --> 00:50:34,924
♪ We never thought it was possible ♪

918
00:50:35,716 --> 00:50:38,218
♪ But here it is coming true ♪

919
00:50:38,302 --> 00:50:40,888
♪ We can have our cake and eat it… ♪

920
00:51:04,869 --> 00:51:08,790
Go on, Brucie! [cheering loudly]

921
00:51:12,043 --> 00:51:13,670
Uh… uh…

922
00:51:15,672 --> 00:51:18,842
[hesitating] Sorry, Miss Trunchbull, I…

923
00:51:18,925 --> 00:51:20,719
[clears throat] …got carried away.

924
00:51:20,802 --> 00:51:22,678
[Agatha] Oh, that's okay, Jenny.

925
00:51:22,762 --> 00:51:25,389
We all get carried away sometimes.

926
00:51:25,473 --> 00:51:26,307
Even me.

927
00:51:36,317 --> 00:51:38,611
Well, come along, Bogtrotter.

928
00:51:39,445 --> 00:51:41,197
-What?
-Oh, did I not mention?

929
00:51:41,947 --> 00:51:43,699
That was the first part
of your punishment, there's more.

930
00:51:43,782 --> 00:51:46,910
There's a second part,
and the second part is Chokey.

931
00:51:49,246 --> 00:51:51,331
Miss Trunchbull, please, you can't!
He's too young.

932
00:51:52,249 --> 00:51:54,417
But I ate it all. I did it. Please!

933
00:51:54,501 --> 00:51:56,336
Not that. Please!

934
00:51:56,419 --> 00:51:58,463
-No!
-[children gasping]

935
00:51:58,546 --> 00:52:01,383
You said if he ate
every crumb he'd be forgiven.

936
00:52:01,466 --> 00:52:04,636
He ate every crumb. We all saw it!

937
00:52:04,719 --> 00:52:06,679
He did it in front of everyone!

938
00:52:06,763 --> 00:52:08,681
You can't just change the rules.

939
00:52:08,765 --> 00:52:11,601
That's not right. It's cheating!

940
00:52:13,020 --> 00:52:14,479
You just said…

941
00:52:16,398 --> 00:52:17,315
"No."

942
00:52:18,775 --> 00:52:19,817
To me.

943
00:52:19,901 --> 00:52:22,194
[breath shaking]

944
00:52:24,322 --> 00:52:26,032
-Come on, Bogtrotter.
-Please!

945
00:52:31,829 --> 00:52:33,080
(off) -Come on!
-No!

946
00:52:33,164 --> 00:52:35,207
Wormwood will be dealt with in due course.

947
00:52:35,291 --> 00:52:37,960
As will the rest of these maggots.

948
00:52:38,044 --> 00:52:40,087
[Bruce] I ate it. I ate it all.

949
00:52:40,171 --> 00:52:42,131
No, please, Miss Trunchbull!

950
00:52:42,214 --> 00:52:43,757
Not the Chokey!

951
00:52:44,425 --> 00:52:45,551
I ate every crumb.

952
00:52:45,634 --> 00:52:47,178
Please!

953
00:52:47,261 --> 00:52:50,431
Not the Chokey! Please, not the Chokey!

954
00:52:54,226 --> 00:52:58,439
[Agatha, over PA]
You see, children, I will always win.

955
00:52:58,522 --> 00:53:01,107
And you will always lose.

956
00:53:01,983 --> 00:53:06,071
Because you are weak, tiny, titchy…

957
00:53:06,655 --> 00:53:08,449
and insignificant.

958
00:53:12,243 --> 00:53:14,495
[children chattering, indistinct]

959
00:53:16,164 --> 00:53:17,540
♪ When I grow up ♪

960
00:53:20,335 --> 00:53:24,464
♪ I will be tall enough
To reach the branches ♪

961
00:53:24,547 --> 00:53:28,259
♪ That I need to reach
To climb the trees ♪

962
00:53:28,343 --> 00:53:31,596
♪ You get to climb when you're grown up ♪

963
00:53:34,515 --> 00:53:36,058
♪ And when I grow up ♪

964
00:53:39,395 --> 00:53:43,023
♪ I will be smart enough to answer all ♪

965
00:53:43,107 --> 00:53:46,068
♪ The questions that you need to know ♪

966
00:53:46,151 --> 00:53:49,947
♪ The answers to before you're grown up ♪

967
00:53:53,283 --> 00:53:57,913
♪ And when I grow up
I will eat sweets every day ♪

968
00:53:57,997 --> 00:54:04,419
♪ On the way to work and I
Will go to bed late every night ♪

969
00:54:05,712 --> 00:54:10,134
♪ And I will wake up
When the sun comes up and I ♪

970
00:54:10,217 --> 00:54:14,138
♪ Will watch cartoons
Until my eyes go square ♪

971
00:54:14,221 --> 00:54:18,725
♪ And I won't care
'Cause I'll be all grown up ♪

972
00:54:19,518 --> 00:54:23,563
♪ When I grow up ♪

973
00:54:24,188 --> 00:54:25,899
[motorcycle engine revving]

974
00:54:27,651 --> 00:54:29,152
♪ When I grow up ♪

975
00:54:29,235 --> 00:54:32,030
-♪ When I grow up ♪
-♪ When I grow up ♪

976
00:54:32,113 --> 00:54:35,574
♪ I will be strong enough to carry all ♪

977
00:54:35,658 --> 00:54:38,244
♪ The heavy things you have to haul ♪

978
00:54:38,327 --> 00:54:42,415
♪ Around with you when you're a grown up ♪

979
00:54:45,751 --> 00:54:47,420
♪ And when I grow up ♪

980
00:54:47,503 --> 00:54:50,506
-♪ When I grow up ♪
-♪ When I grow up ♪

981
00:54:50,589 --> 00:54:54,260
♪ I will be brave enough
To fight the creatures ♪

982
00:54:54,343 --> 00:54:57,888
♪ That you have to fight beneath the bed ♪

983
00:54:57,971 --> 00:55:01,224
♪ Each night to be a grown up ♪

984
00:55:02,518 --> 00:55:05,563
♪ And when I grow up ♪

985
00:55:05,646 --> 00:55:08,982
♪ I will have treats every day ♪

986
00:55:09,066 --> 00:55:11,819
♪ And I'll play with things
That Mum pretends ♪

987
00:55:11,902 --> 00:55:14,571
♪ That mums don't think are fun ♪

988
00:55:14,654 --> 00:55:17,783
♪ And I will wake up ♪

989
00:55:17,866 --> 00:55:20,493
♪ When the sun comes up and I ♪

990
00:55:20,577 --> 00:55:24,331
♪ Will spend all day
Just lying in the sun ♪

991
00:55:24,414 --> 00:55:29,294
♪ And I won't burn
'Cause I'll be all grown up ♪

