♪ When I grow up ♪

993
00:55:53,317 --> 00:55:54,693
♪ When I grow up ♪

994
00:55:58,447 --> 00:56:02,659
♪ I will be brave enough
To fight the creatures ♪

995
00:56:02,743 --> 00:56:06,455
♪ That you have to fight beneath the bed ♪

996
00:56:06,538 --> 00:56:11,042
♪ Each night to be a grown up ♪

997
00:56:12,419 --> 00:56:13,504
♪ When I grow up ♪

998
00:56:13,587 --> 00:56:16,798
♪ Just because you find
That life's not fair ♪

999
00:56:16,882 --> 00:56:21,136
♪ It doesn't mean that you just have to
Grin and bear it ♪

1000
00:56:21,219 --> 00:56:24,681
♪ If you always take it on the chin
And wear it ♪

1001
00:56:24,765 --> 00:56:27,142
♪ Nothing will change ♪

1002
00:56:27,934 --> 00:56:29,102
[Miss Honey] ♪ When I grow up ♪

1003
00:56:29,185 --> 00:56:32,773
[Matilda] ♪ Just because I find myself
In this story ♪

1004
00:56:32,856 --> 00:56:36,526
♪ It doesn't mean that everything
Is written for me ♪

1005
00:56:36,609 --> 00:56:40,113
♪ If I think the ending is fixed already ♪

1006
00:56:40,196 --> 00:56:44,284
♪ I might as well be saying
I think that it's okay ♪

1007
00:56:45,535 --> 00:56:48,663
Mrs. Phelps! Where's the revenge section?

1008
00:56:48,746 --> 00:56:53,000
Well, we don't have a revenge section.
Is it a bully?

1009
00:56:53,584 --> 00:56:56,796
'Cause you know the best way
to deal with bullies is tell someone.

1010
00:56:57,380 --> 00:57:00,049
Straight away. They thrive on silence.

1011
00:57:00,633 --> 00:57:04,011
Tell a teacher.
Or better still, the headmistress.

1012
00:57:04,970 --> 00:57:07,556
I think I've got the next part
of the story.

1013
00:57:07,640 --> 00:57:08,933
But I shall warn you,

1014
00:57:10,059 --> 00:57:11,435
it's about to get real.

1015
00:57:12,812 --> 00:57:13,813
[crowd gasping]

1016
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:18,858
[Matilda] Slowly, the acrobat
tied her shiny white scarf

1017
00:57:18,943 --> 00:57:20,527
around her husband's wrist.

1018
00:57:21,278 --> 00:57:22,904
For luck, my love.

1019
00:57:23,780 --> 00:57:27,326
[Matilda] Then she hugged him
with the biggest hug in the world.

1020
00:57:27,409 --> 00:57:31,580
So hard that he felt that
she could hug all the air out of him.

1021
00:57:31,663 --> 00:57:32,831
[roaring]

1022
00:57:34,123 --> 00:57:36,335
[Matilda] And so they prepared themselves

1023
00:57:36,418 --> 00:57:39,921
for the most dangerous feat
that had ever been performed.

1024
00:57:40,004 --> 00:57:42,924
[band playing suspenseful music]

1025
00:57:59,107 --> 00:58:02,985
The great escapologist had to somehow
escape from the padlocks,

1026
00:58:03,069 --> 00:58:08,449
break free from the cage, and attempt
to rescue his wife within 12 seconds.

1027
00:58:08,532 --> 00:58:11,285
Or she would be blown to bits!

1028
00:58:21,962 --> 00:58:23,255
[breathing heavily]

1029
00:58:26,383 --> 00:58:30,846
[Matilda] The moment the fuse was lit,
the acrobat swung into the air.

1030
00:58:30,929 --> 00:58:33,140
-One second, two seconds…
-[grunting]

1031
00:58:33,223 --> 00:58:34,724
…the crowd held their breath

1032
00:58:34,807 --> 00:58:39,812
as she swung higher and higher
above the sharks and spiky objects!

1033
00:58:39,896 --> 00:58:42,023
Three seconds, four seconds.

1034
00:58:42,107 --> 00:58:44,526
The evil sister looked on gleefully.

1035
00:58:44,609 --> 00:58:46,903
-Five seconds, six seconds.
-[grunting loudly]

1036
00:58:46,986 --> 00:58:49,113
The escapologist
couldn't take his eyes from his wife

1037
00:58:49,196 --> 00:58:51,324
as he struggled in his chains,

1038
00:58:51,408 --> 00:58:54,326
knowing that the tiniest, weeniest mistake

1039
00:58:54,411 --> 00:58:57,288
would mean that he'd lose her
and their child forever.

1040
00:58:57,914 --> 00:58:59,999
Seven seconds, and suddenly…

1041
00:59:00,082 --> 00:59:02,334
-[yells loudly]
-[Matilda] She let go!

1042
00:59:06,130 --> 00:59:09,175
The escapologist reached out
with one huge, massive arm

1043
00:59:09,258 --> 00:59:10,509
to catch his wife and the child.

1044
00:59:10,592 --> 00:59:12,303
-[acrobat gasps]
-[grunts]

1045
00:59:12,386 --> 00:59:14,221
-[Matilda] Eight seconds!
-No, I can't look.

1046
00:59:14,305 --> 00:59:17,433
Nine seconds! Ten seconds! And…

1047
00:59:18,100 --> 00:59:21,478
And… And… Eleven seconds!

1048
00:59:21,562 --> 00:59:26,233
He grabbed the dynamite
and flung it far, far away!

1049
00:59:26,317 --> 00:59:30,236
Hurray! So this story does
have a happy ending after all.

1050
00:59:31,071 --> 00:59:31,905
No.

1051
00:59:33,574 --> 00:59:34,491
No, it doesn't.

1052
00:59:35,742 --> 00:59:37,243
[crowd gasping]

1053
00:59:37,327 --> 00:59:38,579
[acrobat exclaims]

1054
00:59:47,796 --> 00:59:50,966
No! Was she okay? Did she survive?

1055
00:59:51,549 --> 00:59:54,219
She broke every bone in her body.

1056
00:59:54,885 --> 00:59:57,097
Except the ones at the ends
of her little fingers.

1057
00:59:58,056 --> 01:00:00,975
She did manage to live long enough
to have their child.

1058
01:00:01,058 --> 01:00:03,478
[baby fussing]

1059
01:00:04,895 --> 01:00:06,564
But the effort was too great.

1060
01:00:08,148 --> 01:00:09,775
Love our girl.

1061
01:00:11,444 --> 01:00:14,989
Love our daughter with all your heart.

1062
01:00:16,616 --> 01:00:19,409
She is all we ever wanted.

1063
01:00:26,208 --> 01:00:28,127
[crying softly]

1064
01:00:29,669 --> 01:00:30,838
And then she died.

1065
01:00:33,673 --> 01:00:34,716
And then…

1066
01:00:35,717 --> 01:00:37,094
things got worse.

1067
01:00:37,177 --> 01:00:38,720
What? Worse?

1068
01:00:38,803 --> 01:00:40,389
I'm afraid they did.

1069
01:00:40,472 --> 01:00:42,849
Because the escapologist was so kind

1070
01:00:42,932 --> 01:00:47,020
that he never for one second blamed
the evil stepsister for what happened.

1071
01:00:47,896 --> 01:00:52,692
In fact, he asked her to move in
and help look after his daughter.

1072
01:00:52,776 --> 01:00:55,153
[Mrs. Phelps] No, no,
don't ask her to move in.

1073
01:00:55,236 --> 01:00:57,488
She was nothing but cruel
to the little girl,

1074
01:00:57,572 --> 01:01:00,700
making her wash and clean
all day long. Shouting,

1075
01:01:00,784 --> 01:01:03,202
[Matilda and stepsister]
"Clean the floor and I'll be nice!"

1076
01:01:03,286 --> 01:01:06,455
When the little girl did clean it,
she was even crueler

1077
01:01:06,539 --> 01:01:09,417
because she was
a terrible, terrible cheat!

1078
01:01:09,500 --> 01:01:10,626
I hate cheats!

1079
01:01:10,709 --> 01:01:14,672
All in secret, so the escapologist
never suspected a thing.

1080
01:01:14,755 --> 01:01:17,758
And so the poor little girl grew up
with the meanest, cruelest,

1081
01:01:17,841 --> 01:01:20,886
horriblest aunt
you could possibly imagine!

1082
01:01:20,969 --> 01:01:23,055
Let's call the police! [panting]

1083
01:01:24,056 --> 01:01:25,223
Mrs. Phelps.

1084
01:01:26,141 --> 01:01:27,685
It's just a story.

1085
01:01:28,268 --> 01:01:29,144
What?

1086
01:01:31,354 --> 01:01:33,732
Oh. Yes, of course.

1087
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:35,400
A story.

1088
01:01:36,193 --> 01:01:38,528
It's just, you make it so real.

1089
01:01:39,404 --> 01:01:41,114
[relieved laugh] Your mind, Matilda.

1090
01:01:41,614 --> 01:01:45,077
Your parents must think they've won
the lottery with a child like you.

1091
01:01:45,702 --> 01:01:47,745
Oh… they do.

1092
01:01:48,705 --> 01:01:50,290
They're always saying that.

1093
01:01:50,373 --> 01:01:52,875
In fact, they say,

1094
01:01:52,960 --> 01:01:56,546
"We're so proud of you, Matilda,
you're like winning the…"

1095
01:02:00,383 --> 01:02:02,802
Yeah. I'd better go.

1096
01:02:05,263 --> 01:02:07,599
[shrieking]

1097
01:02:07,682 --> 01:02:10,893
It's just like winning the lottery!

1098
01:02:10,977 --> 01:02:11,978
What?

1099
01:02:12,604 --> 01:02:13,771
Me?

1100
01:02:13,855 --> 01:02:16,315
You? No, you're like
eating someone else's bogeys.

1101
01:02:16,398 --> 01:02:18,651
Like winning a snottery, you, boy.

1102
01:02:18,735 --> 01:02:19,777
I'm a girl.

1103
01:02:19,861 --> 01:02:21,612
But how, Harry?

1104
01:02:21,696 --> 01:02:23,280
Remember that big, muscly idiot?

1105
01:02:23,364 --> 01:02:26,033
Turns out he had a whole lot
of muscly mates.

1106
01:02:26,117 --> 01:02:27,701
Bucketloads of cash.

1107
01:02:27,784 --> 01:02:30,121
Everyone wanting a luxury car.

1108
01:02:30,204 --> 01:02:34,375
All I had was a load of old bangers,
each with 100,000 miles on the clock.

1109
01:02:34,458 --> 01:02:37,461
So, I did what any decent
business leader would.

1110
01:02:37,544 --> 01:02:38,587
What?

1111
01:02:38,670 --> 01:02:39,963
I bought a drill.

1112
01:02:40,046 --> 01:02:43,967
Attached it to the speedometer
and whacked it in reverse.

1113
01:02:44,050 --> 01:02:46,512
I put back the mileage
on every one of those cars

1114
01:02:46,595 --> 01:02:50,181
and sold them to those big,
muscly idiots, resulting in…

1115
01:02:50,265 --> 01:02:51,975
Money!

1116
01:02:52,058 --> 01:02:53,184
But you cheated them!

1117
01:02:54,519 --> 01:02:55,436
Excuse me?

1118
01:02:55,520 --> 01:02:58,982
You cheated them.
What you did, it wasn't right.

1119
01:02:59,065 --> 01:03:00,525
You're just a cheat!

1120
01:03:01,109 --> 01:03:03,486
Oh, the little pig!

1121
01:03:04,612 --> 01:03:07,991
It's the books, Harry.
It's the books and the stories.

1122
01:03:08,074 --> 01:03:09,367
Is it now?

1123
01:03:10,243 --> 01:03:11,077
Books, is it?

1124
01:03:13,871 --> 01:03:15,623
You know what I'm going to do tomorrow?

1125
01:03:16,124 --> 01:03:17,708
I'm going to go down to that library,

1126
01:03:18,501 --> 01:03:22,880
I'm going to tell that old bag
to never let you in again.

1127
01:03:22,963 --> 01:03:24,256
What?

1128
01:03:24,340 --> 01:03:27,134
Always sticking your nose in
where it don't belong.

1129
01:03:27,885 --> 01:03:32,014
You nasty little creep!

1130
01:03:32,097 --> 01:03:33,098
[gasping]

1131
01:03:40,105 --> 01:03:44,818
That night, the escapologist's daughter
cried herself to sleep.

1132
01:03:44,902 --> 01:03:48,613
She never said a word
about the evil step-aunt's bullying.

1133
01:03:48,697 --> 01:03:51,033
She didn't want to add
to her father's pain.

1134
01:03:51,741 --> 01:03:55,245
This only encouraged the woman
to greater cruelties,

1135
01:03:55,329 --> 01:03:58,665
until one day she exploded.

1136
01:03:59,416 --> 01:04:02,210
[Agatha and Matilda] Sticking your
nose in where it doesn't belong!

1137
01:04:02,294 --> 01:04:04,629
You nasty little creep!

1138
01:04:04,713 --> 01:04:07,841
And she threw her…
threw her into a dank,

1139
01:04:07,924 --> 01:04:11,469
dark, dusty cellar,
locked the door and went out.

1140
01:04:11,553 --> 01:04:13,429
[car approaching]

1141
01:04:14,598 --> 01:04:18,267
But that night, the escapologist
happened to come home early.

1142
01:04:19,853 --> 01:04:22,730
And when he heard the sound
of his daughter's tears,

1143
01:04:22,814 --> 01:04:25,191
-he smashed the door open.
-[yelling]

1144
01:04:28,694 --> 01:04:32,698
[escapologist] ♪ Don't cry ♪

1145
01:04:33,282 --> 01:04:36,910
♪ I am here, little girl ♪

1146
01:04:36,994 --> 01:04:41,039
♪ Please don't cry
Dry your eyes ♪

1147
01:04:41,123 --> 01:04:46,378
♪ Wipe away your tears, little girl ♪

1148
01:04:46,462 --> 01:04:49,089
♪ Forgive me ♪

1149
01:04:49,840 --> 01:04:53,343
♪ I didn't mean to desert you ♪

1150
01:04:55,345 --> 01:04:58,431
♪ Don't cry, little girl ♪

1151
01:04:59,141 --> 01:05:01,309
♪ Nothing can hurt you ♪

1152
01:05:01,393 --> 01:05:04,812
♪ You've nothing to fear ♪

1153
01:05:06,689 --> 01:05:10,277
♪ I'm here ♪

1154
01:05:11,819 --> 01:05:13,113
[thunder rumbling]

1155
01:05:13,196 --> 01:05:15,698
[both] Have I been
so wrapped up in my grief

1156
01:05:15,782 --> 01:05:17,617
that I've forgotten the thing
that matters most?

1157
01:05:18,200 --> 01:05:20,995
I love you so much, my daughter.

1158
01:05:21,078 --> 01:05:24,331
I shall spend the rest of my life
making it up to you.

1159
01:05:32,882 --> 01:05:35,259
♪ Don't cry, Daddy ♪

1160
01:05:38,179 --> 01:05:40,932
♪ I'm all right, Daddy ♪

1161
01:05:41,515 --> 01:05:43,475
♪ Please don't cry ♪

1162
01:05:43,559 --> 01:05:46,979
♪ Here, let me wipe away your tears ♪

1163
01:05:50,774 --> 01:05:52,359
♪ Forgive me ♪

1164
01:05:52,443 --> 01:05:54,236
♪ Daddy, forgive me ♪

1165
01:05:54,320 --> 01:05:56,572
♪ I didn't mean to desert you ♪

1166
01:05:56,655 --> 01:05:59,074
♪ I didn't want to upset you ♪

1167
01:05:59,157 --> 01:06:01,743
-♪ Please, Daddy, don't cry ♪
-♪ Don't cry, little girl ♪

1168
01:06:01,827 --> 01:06:06,122
-♪ I'll be all right with you by my side ♪
-♪ Nothing will hurt you ♪

1169
01:06:06,206 --> 01:06:09,042
-♪ I have nothing to fear ♪
-♪ You've nothing to fear ♪

1170
01:06:11,878 --> 01:06:14,630
-♪ You're here ♪
-♪ I'm here ♪

1171
01:06:16,967 --> 01:06:19,135
[Matilda] But when the little girl slept,

1172
01:06:19,219 --> 01:06:22,931
the escapologist's thoughts
turned to the evil stepsister

1173
01:06:23,014 --> 01:06:26,059
and a mighty rage
grew inside his great heart!

1174
01:06:26,642 --> 01:06:29,019
This demon, this monster.

1175
01:06:29,104 --> 01:06:30,938
Bullying children is her game, is it?

1176
01:06:31,606 --> 01:06:33,899
[Matilda] And as the unfairness
of the aunt's cruelty

1177
01:06:33,983 --> 01:06:35,901
spun around inside him,

1178
01:06:35,985 --> 01:06:39,780
it swirled and whirled
into a great storm of fury

1179
01:06:39,864 --> 01:06:42,492
that his mind could no longer contain.

1180
01:06:49,624 --> 01:06:52,459
And that was the last
the little girl ever saw of him.

1181
01:06:53,919 --> 01:06:57,923
Because he never came home, ever again.

1182
01:07:00,926 --> 01:07:02,928
-[metal creaking]
-[light gasp]

1183
01:07:11,895 --> 01:07:13,647
[Eric] Can you do telekenipsis?

1184
01:07:14,231 --> 01:07:16,316
It's where you have loads of brains.

1185
01:07:16,400 --> 01:07:18,234
They squish out through your eyes

1186
01:07:18,317 --> 01:07:20,695
and you can move things with your mind.

1187
01:07:24,533 --> 01:07:27,118
[crows cawing]

1188
01:07:27,201 --> 01:07:29,203
[indistinct chatter]

1189
01:07:34,918 --> 01:07:37,711
Matilda. This is for you.

1190
01:07:40,798 --> 01:07:41,799
Thank you.

1191
01:07:41,882 --> 01:07:44,802
[whispering] Matilda, here you are.

1192
01:07:48,264 --> 01:07:50,474
[children chattering in hushed tones]

1193
01:07:51,392 --> 01:07:53,686
Isn't it a splendid day, old pal?

1194
01:07:53,769 --> 01:07:56,939
-Lavender, what is going on?
-You, you're a hero.

1195
01:07:57,022 --> 01:07:58,148
Here, Matilda.

1196
01:07:59,483 --> 01:08:01,694
Egg and cress, Stephanie? Really!

1197
01:08:03,320 --> 01:08:04,487
A hero?

1198
01:08:04,572 --> 01:08:06,990
Yes. You're leading a revolution.

1199
01:08:07,074 --> 01:08:10,243
-What revolution?
-You said "no" to The Trunchbull.

1200
01:08:10,327 --> 01:08:12,412
See, no one's done that before.

1201
01:08:16,333 --> 01:08:18,293
[Lavender] You're leading a revolution.

1202
01:08:18,376 --> 01:08:20,045
You said "no" to The Trunchbull.

1203
01:08:20,712 --> 01:08:22,380
No one's done that before.

1204
01:08:22,880 --> 01:08:25,467
-[laughter]
-[all playing chaotic music]

1205
01:08:28,303 --> 01:08:29,637
Ready for a little fun?

1206
01:08:29,721 --> 01:08:30,972
[all] Yeah!

1207
01:08:31,055 --> 01:08:32,849
-Fun?
-[cheering ceases]

1208
01:08:32,932 --> 01:08:34,684
Did you say "fun"?

1209
01:08:36,978 --> 01:08:38,438
[snaps fingers]

1210
01:08:40,607 --> 01:08:43,901
[Agatha] It is not our job
to make things fun.

1211
01:08:43,985 --> 01:08:47,947
We are not here to encourage or nurture.

1212
01:08:48,030 --> 01:08:50,699
We are here to crush them until…

1213
01:08:51,784 --> 01:08:53,828
the wriggling stops.

1214
01:08:53,911 --> 01:08:58,207
Well, I… I don't actually
believe that… that the--

1215
01:08:58,290 --> 01:09:02,211
D-d-d-do you, Jenny?
D-d-d-do you think anyone c-c-c-cares?

1216
01:09:03,379 --> 01:09:06,507
This class is full of rebels,

1217
01:09:07,090 --> 01:09:09,926
and they need a real lesson.

1218
01:09:10,511 --> 01:09:13,389
Bring your gym gear
and change on the way.

1219
01:09:13,472 --> 01:09:14,806
You see, Jenny,

1220
01:09:14,890 --> 01:09:17,934
to teach the child, we must first break…

1221
01:09:18,935 --> 01:09:20,061
the child.

1222
01:09:22,523 --> 01:09:24,858
♪ This school of late
Has started reeking ♪

1223
01:09:24,941 --> 01:09:27,110
♪ Quiet maggot, when I'm speaking! ♪

1224
01:09:27,193 --> 01:09:29,570
♪ Reeking with a most disturbing scent ♪

1225
01:09:30,655 --> 01:09:32,448
♪ Only the finest nostrils smell it ♪

1226
01:09:32,532 --> 01:09:34,034
-♪ But I know it oh, too well ♪
-[boy yelps]

1227
01:09:34,117 --> 01:09:37,787
♪ It is the odor of rebellion
It's the bouquet of dissent ♪

1228
01:09:37,870 --> 01:09:40,748
♪ And you may bet your britches
This headmistress ♪

1229
01:09:40,831 --> 01:09:42,792
♪ Finds this foul odifer-ous-ness ♪

1230
01:09:42,875 --> 01:09:46,296
♪ Wholly olfactorily insulting ♪

1231
01:09:46,379 --> 01:09:49,507
♪ And so to stop the stench's spread ♪

1232
01:09:49,590 --> 01:09:52,760
♪ I find a session of Phys-Ed ♪

1233
01:09:53,344 --> 01:09:58,057
♪ Sorts the merely rank
From the revolting ♪

1234
01:09:59,058 --> 01:10:00,560
Come along, squits.

1235
01:10:00,643 --> 01:10:02,562
I'll take it from here, Jenny!

1236
01:10:05,731 --> 01:10:09,819
♪ The smell of rebellion
Comes out in the sweat ♪

1237
01:10:09,902 --> 01:10:13,363
♪ And Phys-Ed will get you sweating ♪

1238
01:10:13,447 --> 01:10:17,952
♪ And it won't be long
Before I smell the pong ♪

1239
01:10:18,035 --> 01:10:20,620
♪ Of aiding and abetting ♪

1240
01:10:21,705 --> 01:10:24,874
♪ Before a weed becomes
Too big and greedy ♪

1241
01:10:24,958 --> 01:10:26,876
♪ You really need to nip it in the bud ♪

1242
01:10:29,045 --> 01:10:31,172
♪ Before the worm starts to turn ♪

1243
01:10:31,255 --> 01:10:33,383
-[yells]
